divs: Sighting DetailsMy wife and I were on the back porch. I just showed her Venus in the SW sky. Then something caught the corner of my eye. It was high in the eastern sky. It was the same size as Venus and brighter. No sound came from it and it kept going in a Easterly direction for about 3 minutes. We looked through it with Hi Powered binocular's. It was not a plane. I ran out to the front yard to get a unobstructed view. Then it disappeared like someone turning off a light switch. Last point of view was still high in the Eastern sky.
